<br>
Hypothetical example:<br>
<br>
-NToV/VexThal loot XXXX with effect Spell Haste 3 and a bunch of other decent stats.<br>
<br>
-PoP Mage summoned item XXXX with effect Spell Haste 4 and some minor stats<br>
<br>
The latter is superior in the simple fact that it will focus beyond level 60.  The SH3 on the NToV/VT loot just became obsolete when that player dinged 61(one kill on day of release).  To focus their new spells they take off the uber loot and put on a summoned ring.<br>
<br>
I think this is wrong.  I thought it was the first time around, and I think it is even worse now.<br>
<br>
Focii should never have scaled with level, they should have scaled with effect: IE spell haste 1 = 5 percent, spell haste 2 = 10 percent, spell haste 3 = 20 percent etc etc.  Having an item become auto-obsolete just because you dinged a 'tier' level is absurd.<br>
<br>
Focus Effect 3 should scale to 65, and scrap this new batch of summons, since it is likely we will get those instead of something else.<br>
<br>
Sage Finraziel<br>
